  "prompt": "What is the difference between objective and subjective?",
  "response": "Here's a breakdown of the key differences between objective and subjective:\n\nObjective:\n- Based on facts, data, and measurable evidence\n- Independent of personal feelings or opinions\n- Can be verified by different people\n- Aims to be unbiased and neutral\n- Focuses on observable, concrete information\n- Examples: Scientific measurements, mathematical calculations\n\nSubjective:\n- Based on personal feelings, opinions, or interpretations\n- Influenced by individual perspectives and emotions\n- Can vary from person to person\n- Reflects personal bias and individual experience\n- Focuses on personal perception and judgment\n- Examples: Art criticism, taste in music, personal preferences\n\nIn simple terms:\n- Objective = factual and universal\n- Subjective = personal and variable",
